    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1899-11-28T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1899-11-28T00:00:00-05:00" n="759"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d759">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Hay</persName> to Lord <persName
                            type="to">Pauncefote</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1899-11-28">
                            <hi rend="italic">November 28, 1899</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 1619.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Excellency</hi>: I have the honor to acknowledge the
                    receipt of your note of the 22d instant on the subject of remitting money to
                    British prisoners in the Transvaal, in which, under instructions from your
                    Government, you suggest that the United States consul at Pretoria should point
                    out to the Transvaal Government that they are departing from the usual practice
                    in not allowing the friendly offices of the United States consul to be used on
                    behalf of these prisoners.</p>
                <p>I have instructed the consul at Pretoria to call the attention of the Government
                    of the South African Republic to the statements and views of Lord Salisbury.</p>
                <p>I have, etc.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">John Hay.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
